import { useEffect, useState } from "react" import { useNavigate } from "react-router-dom" import "./BookingForm.css" export const BookingForm = () => { const [genres, setGenres] = useState([]) const [bookingForm, setBookingForm] = useState({ id: 0, genreId: 0, startDate: "", endDate: "", numOfSongs: "", musicianRequest: true, photoRequest: true }) const navigate = useNavigate() const localFatBackUser = localStorage.getItem("fatback_user") const fatbackUserObject = JSON.parse(localFatBackUser) useEffect( () => { fetch(`http://localhost:8088/genres`) .then(response => response.json()) .then((genreArray) => { setGenres(genreArray) }) }, [] ) const submitButtonClick = (event) => { event.preventDefault() const requestFormToSendToAPI = { id: fatbackUserObject.id, genreId: 0, startDate: "", endDate: "", numOfSongs: "", musicianRequest: "true", sessionMusicians: "true", photoRequest: "true", videoRequest: "true" } return fetch(`http://localhost:8088/bookingRequest`, { method: "POST", headers: { "Cotent-Type": "application/json", }, body: JSON.stringify(requestFormToSendToAPI) }) .then(response => response.json()) .then(() => { navigate("/booking/myrequest") }) } return ( < div className="bookingForm" >
